[0m[49m[39m  156, 161[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  157, 162[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  158, 163[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  159, 164[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  160, 165[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 161     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Services** | Lambda, ECS (Fargate), DynamoDB, EventBridge, SQS, S3, API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 162     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `ecs:RunTask`, `dynamodb:GetItem/PutItem/Query`, `s3:GetObject/PutObject`, `sqs:SendMessage/ReceiveMessage`, `events:PutEvents` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Lambda, ECS (Fargate), DynamoDB, EventBridge, SQS (FIFO), S3, API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `ecs:RunTask`, `dynamodb:GetItem/PutItem/Query`, `s3:GetObject/PutObject`, `sqs:SendMessage/ReceiveMessage`, `events:PutEvents`. All permissions scoped to specific resource ARNs (e.g., solver ECS task role accesses only the case and schedule DynamoDB tables, the historical data S3 bucket, and the replan SQS queue). |
[0m[49m[39m  163, 168[0m:[39m[49m | **BAA** | Required: case data includes patient identifiers and procedure details (PHI) |
[0m[49m[39m  164, 169[0m:[39m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; all transit over TLS; ECS task roles with least-privilege |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 165     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Fargate tasks in private subnets with VPC endpoints for DynamoDB, S3, SQS, CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Fargate tasks in private subnets with VPC endpoints for DynamoDB, S3, SQS, EventBridge, and CloudWatch Logs. Lambda functions that handle PHI payloads should also be VPC-attached; lightweight orchestration Lambdas can run outside the VPC with appropriate IAM controls. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **EHR Integration** | Secured network path required for PHI-bearing inbound connection: AWS Direct Connect, site-to-site VPN, or API Gateway with mutual TLS. HL7v2 via MLLP-to-HTTPS adapter in a private subnet. FHIR APIs via OAuth 2.0 with SMART on FHIR scopes. |
[0m[49m[39m  166, 172[0m:[39m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled for all API calls; schedule changes auditable |
[0m[49m[39m  167, 173[0m:[39m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic surgical case lists. Use realistic procedure mixes and durations from published OR benchmarking data. Never use real patient data in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 168     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Fargate solver: ~$0.05-0.20 per optimization run (2-4 vCPU, 8 GB, 1-10 min). Lambda + DynamoDB: negligible. Monthly: $200-800 depending on replan frequency. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Fargate solver: ~$0.05-0.20 per optimization run (2-4 vCPU, 8 GB, 1-10 min). Lambda + DynamoDB: negligible. Monthly with open-source solvers (OR-Tools CP-SAT, HiGHS): $200-800 depending on replan frequency. With commercial solvers (Gurobi, CPLEX): add $1,500-5,000/month for cloud licensing depending on usage volume and contract terms. Commercial solvers are not required for most hospital-scale problems (under 100 cases/day). |
[0m[49m[39m  169, 175[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  170, 176[0m:[39m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[39m  171, 177[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  172, 178[0m:[39m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[39m  173, 179[0m:[39m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[39m  174, 180[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Constraint building, duration prediction, replan trigger logic |
[0m[49m[39m  175, 181[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon ECS (Fargate)** | Runs the optimization solver (CP-SAT, HiGHS, or commercial) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 176     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Stores case data, constraints, and current optimized schedule |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Stores case data, constraints, current optimized schedule, and manual overrides |
[0m[49m[39m  177, 183[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon EventBridge** | Routes real-time surgical events (completions, cancellations, add-ons) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 178     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon SQS** | Buffers replan requests to prevent concurrent optimization conflicts |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SQS (FIFO)** | Buffers replan requests with deduplication to prevent concurrent optimization conflicts |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SQS (DLQ)** | Captures failed replan attempts after 3 retries; triggers CloudWatch alarm for manual intervention |
[0m[49m[39m  179, 186[0m:[39m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Historical case data, duration models, optimization audit logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 180     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Amazon API Gateway** | Exposes schedule API for dashboard and EHR integration |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon API Gateway** | Exposes schedule API for dashboard and EHR integration (with authorizer for role-based access) |
[0m[49m[39m  181, 188[0m:[39m[49m | **AWS KMS** | Encryption key management for PHI at rest |
[0m[49m[39m  182, 189[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  183, 190[0m:[39m[49m ### Code
[0m[49m[39m  184, 191[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  185, 192[0m:[39m[49m #### Walkthrough
[0m[49m[39m  186, 193[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  187, 194[0m:[39m[49m **Step 1: Ingest and enrich case data.** When the daily case list is finalized (typically by 4-5 PM the day before), the system pulls each case's details and enriches them with predicted duration, equipment needs, and constraint metadata. The duration prediction uses historical data for the specific procedure-surgeon combination. This enrichment step is what transforms a simple case list into an optimization-ready dataset. Skip it and the solver has no basis for intelligent sequencing.
[0m[49m[39m  188, 195[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  189, 196[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  190, 197[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION enrich_case_list(raw_cases):
[0m[49m[39m  191, 198[0m:[39m[49m     // Pull the confirmed case list and add optimization-relevant metadata.
[0m[49m[39m  192, 199[0m:[39m[49m     enriched = empty list
[0m[49m[39m  193, 200[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  194, 201[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each case in raw_cases:
[0m[49m[39m  195, 202[0m:[39m[49m         // Predict duration using historical procedure-surgeon data.
[0m[49m[39m  196, 203[0m:[39m[49m         // The prediction includes mean and standard deviation for buffer calculation.
[0m[49m[39m  197, 204[0m:[39m[49m         duration_estimate = predict_duration(
[0m[49m[39m  198, 205[0m:[39m[49m             procedure_code = case.cpt_code,
[0m[49m[39m  199, 206[0m:[39m[49m             surgeon_id     = case.surgeon_id,
[0m[49m[39m  200, 207[0m:[39m[49m             patient_asa    = case.asa_class    // sicker patients take longer
[0m[49m[39m  201, 208[0m:[39m[49m         )
[0m[49m[39m  202, 209[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  203, 210[0m:[39m[49m         // Look up equipment requirements from the surgeon's preference card.
[0m[49m[39m  204, 211[0m:[39m[49m         equipment_needs = get_preference_card(case.surgeon_id, case.cpt_code)
[0m[49m[39m  205, 212[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  206, 213[0m:[39m[49m         // Build the enriched case record.
[0m[49m[39m  207, 214[0m:[39m[49m         enriched_case = {
[0m[49m[39m  208, 215[0m:[39m[49m             case_id:          case.id,
[0m[49m[39m  209, 216[0m:[39m[49m             procedure:        case.cpt_code,
[0m[49m[39m  210, 217[0m:[39m[49m             surgeon_id:       case.surgeon_id,
[0m[49m[39m  211, 218[0m:[39m[49m             expected_duration: duration_estimate.mean,
[0m[49m[39m  212, 219[0m:[39m[49m             duration_buffer:  duration_estimate.std_dev * 1.2,  // ~90th percentile coverage
[0m[49m[39m  213, 220[0m:[39m[49m             equipment:        equipment_needs.required_equipment,
[0m[49m[39m  214, 221[0m:[39m[49m             room_constraints: equipment_needs.room_requirements,
[0m[49m[39m  215, 222[0m:[39m[49m             patient_constraints: get_patient_constraints(case.patient_id),
[0m[49m[39m  216, 223[0m:[39m[49m             priority:         case.urgency_level,
[0m[49m[39m  217, 224[0m:[39m[49m             turnover_class:   classify_turnover(case.cpt_code)  // clean, contaminated, sterile
[0m[49m[39m  218, 225[0m:[39m[49m         }
[0m[49m[39m  219, 226[0m:[39m[49m         append enriched_case to enriched
[0m[49m[39m  220, 227[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  221, 228[0m:[39m[49m     // Store enriched cases for the solver to consume.
[0m[49m[39m  222, 229[0m:[39m[49m     write enriched to database table "or-cases-today"
[0m[49m[39m  223, 230[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN enriched
[0m[49m[39m  224, 231[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  225, 232[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **A note on PHI in the enriched case table.** The "or-cases-today" DynamoDB table contains PHI: patient identifiers linked to procedure codes and clinical flags (ASA class, immunocompromised status). IAM policies on this table should restrict read access to the solver engine's ECS task role and the constraint builder Lambda. The published schedule API (Step 5) should expose only the minimum necessary: procedure type, surgeon, and timing. Patient identifiers should not flow to the dashboard unless the viewer has a clinical need-to-know. Implement an API Gateway authorizer with role-based access: charge nurses see patient names, the public OR board shows only room/time/procedure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  226, 235[0m:[39m[49m **Step 2: Build the constraint model.** This step translates business rules into mathematical constraints the solver can process. The separation between business rules (which change frequently) and solver logic (which is stable) is intentional. When a new surgeon joins or a room gets renovated, you update the constraint configuration, not the solver code.
[0m[49m[39m  227, 236[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  228, 237[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  229, 238[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION build_constraint_model(cases, rooms, staff_schedules):
[0m[49m[39m  230, 239[0m:[39m[49m     model = new ConstraintModel()
[0m[49m[39m  231, 240[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  232, 241[0m:[39m[49m     // Decision variables: assign each case to a room and a start time.
[0m[49m[39m  233, 242[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each case in cases:
[0m[49m[39m  234, 243[0m:[39m[49m         case.room_var  = model.add_variable(domain = eligible_rooms(case))
[0m[49m[39m  235, 244[0m:[39m[49m         case.start_var = model.add_variable(domain = [block_start_time ... block_end_time])
[0m[49m[39m  236, 245[0m:[39m[49m         case.end_var   = case.start_var + case.expected_duration + case.duration_buffer
[0m[49m[39m  237, 246[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  238, 247[0m:[39m[49m     // Hard constraint: no overlap within a room (including turnover time).
[0m[49m[39m  239, 248[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each pair (case_a, case_b) where case_a != case_b:
[0m[49m[39m  240, 249[0m:[39m[49m         IF case_a.room_var == case_b.room_var:
[0m[49m[39m  241, 250[0m:[39m[49m             model.add_constraint(
[0m[49m[39m  242, 251[0m:[39m[49m                 case_a.end_var + turnover_time(case_a, case_b) <= case_b.start_var
[0m[49m[39m  243, 252[0m:[39m[49m                 OR
[0m[49m[39m  244, 253[0m:[39m[49m                 case_b.end_var + turnover_time(case_b, case_a) <= case_a.start_var
[0m[49m[39m  245, 254[0m:[39m[49m             )
[0m[49m[39m  246, 255[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  247, 256[0m:[39m[49m     // Hard constraint: shared equipment cannot be double-booked.
[0m[49m[39m  248, 257[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each equipment_item in shared_equipment_list:
[0m[49m[39m  249, 258[0m:[39m[49m         cases_needing = filter cases where equipment_item in case.equipment
[0m[49m[39m  250, 259[0m:[39m[49m         FOR each pair in cases_needing:
[0m[49m[39m  251, 260[0m:[39m[49m             model.add_no_overlap_constraint(pair, setup_time = equipment_item.setup_minutes)
[0m[49m[39m  252, 261[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  253, 262[0m:[39m[49m     // Hard constraint: staff availability windows.
[0m[49m[39m  254, 263[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each staff_member in staff_schedules:
[0m[49m[39m  255, 264[0m:[39m[49m         assigned_cases = filter cases covered by staff_member
[0m[49m[39m  256, 265[0m:[39m[49m         FOR each case in assigned_cases:
[0m[49m[39m  257, 266[0m:[39m[49m             model.add_constraint(case.start_var >= staff_member.available_from)
[0m[49m[39m  258, 267[0m:[39m[49m             model.add_constraint(case.end_var <= staff_member.available_until)
[0m[49m[39m  259, 268[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  260, 269[0m:[39m[49m     // Hard constraint: room capability.
[0m[49m[39m  261, 270[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each case in cases:
[0m[49m[39m  262, 271[0m:[39m[49m         model.add_constraint(case.room_var in case.room_constraints)
[0m[49m[39m  263, 272[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Hard constraint: manual overrides (locked assignments from charge nurse).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each override in read_overrides_from_database():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model.fix_variable(override.case_id.room_var, override.locked_room)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         model.fix_variable(override.case_id.start_var, override.locked_start_time)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  264, 278[0m:[39m[49m     // Soft constraint: minimize total overtime (penalized in objective).
[0m[49m[39m  265, 279[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each room in rooms:
[0m[49m[39m  266, 280[0m:[39m[49m         room_end = max(case.end_var for cases assigned to room)
[0m[49m[39m  267, 281[0m:[39m[49m         overtime = max(0, room_end - room.block_end_time)
[0m[49m[39m  268, 282[0m:[39m[49m         model.add_to_objective(overtime * OVERTIME_PENALTY_WEIGHT)
[0m[49m[39m  269, 283[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  270, 284[0m:[39m[49m     // Soft constraint: surgeon sequence preferences.
[0m[49m[39m  271, 285[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each surgeon_preference in surgeon_preferences:
[0m[49m[39m  272, 286[0m:[39m[49m         // e.g., "complex case first" = penalize if complex case isn't position 1
[0m[49m[39m  273, 287[0m:[39m[49m         model.add_soft_penalty(surgeon_preference.violation_cost)
[0m[49m[39m  274, 288[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  275, 289[0m:[39m[49m     // Objective: minimize weighted sum of overtime + idle gaps + preference violations.
[0m[49m[39m  276, 290[0m:[39m[49m     model.set_objective(MINIMIZE)
[0m[49m[39m  277, 291[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  278, 292[0m:[39m[49m     RETURN model
[0m[49m[39m  279, 293[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  280, 294[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  281, 295[0m:[39m[49m **Step 3: Solve.** Hand the model to the solver engine. For batch mode, allow several minutes of compute time to find a high-quality solution. For replan mode, fix already-completed cases and give the solver a tight time limit (10-30 seconds).
[0m[49m[39m  282, 296[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  283, 297[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  284, 298[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION solve_schedule(model, mode):
[0m[49m[39m  285, 299[0m:[39m[49m     IF mode == "batch":
[0m[49m[39m  286, 300[0m:[39m[49m         // Overnight planning: take time to find optimal solution.
[0m[49m[39m  287, 301[0m:[39m[49m         solver = create_solver(type = "CP-SAT")  // or MIP solver for smaller instances
[0m[49m[39m  288, 302[0m:[39m[49m         solver.set_time_limit(300 seconds)        // 5 minutes max
[0m[49m[39m  289, 303[0m:[39m[49m         solver.set_optimality_gap(0.02)           // stop if within 2% of proven optimal
[0m[49m[39m  290, 304[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  291, 305[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE IF mode == "replan":
[0m[49m[39m  292, 306[0m:[39m[49m         // Intraday: need a good answer fast.
[0m[49m[39m  293, 307[0m:[39m[49m         solver = create_solver(type = "CP-SAT")
[0m[49m[39m  294, 308[0m:[39m[49m         solver.set_time_limit(30 seconds)
[0m[49m[39m  295, 309[0m:[39m[49m         // Warm-start: fix cases that have already started or completed.
[0m[49m[39m  296, 310[0m:[39m[49m         FOR each case where case.status in ["in_progress", "completed"]:
[0m[49m[39m  297, 311[0m:[39m[49m             model.fix_variable(case.room_var, case.actual_room)
[0m[49m[39m  298, 312[0m:[39m[49m             model.fix_variable(case.start_var, case.actual_start_time)
[0m[49m[39m  299, 313[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  300, 314[0m:[39m[49m     result = solver.solve(model)
[0m[49m[39m  301, 315[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  302, 316[0m:[39m[49m     IF result.status == "OPTIMAL" or result.status == "FEASIBLE":
[0m[49m[39m  303, 317[0m:[39m[49m         schedule = extract_schedule(result)
[0m[49m[39m  304, 318[0m:[39m[49m         write schedule to database table "or-schedule-current"
[0m[49m[39m  305, 319[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN schedule
[0m[49m[39m  306, 320[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE:
[0m[49m[39m  307, 321[0m:[39m[49m         // No feasible solution found. Constraints are too tight.
[0m[49m[39m  308, 322[0m:[39m[49m         // Return the infeasibility report so humans can decide what to relax.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         log_error("Solver returned INFEASIBLE. Alerting perioperative coordinator.")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         trigger_cloudwatch_alarm("or-solver-infeasible")
[0m[49m[39m  309, 325[0m:[39m[49m         RETURN { status: "INFEASIBLE", conflicts: result.conflict_analysis() }
[0m[49m[39m  310, 326[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  311, 327[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  312, 328[0m:[39m[49m **Step 4: Handle real-time events.** Throughout the day, events arrive: cases finish early or late, cancellations happen, urgent add-ons appear. The replan trigger evaluates whether the disruption is significant enough to warrant re-optimization.
[0m[49m[39m  313, 329[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  314, 330[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  315, 331[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION handle_or_event(event):
[0m[49m[39m  316, 332[0m:[39m[49m     current_schedule = read from database "or-schedule-current"
[0m[49m[39m  317, 333[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  318, 334[0m:[39m[49m     IF event.type == "case_completed":
[0m[49m[39m  319, 335[0m:[39m[49m         // Update actual end time. Check if downstream cases need adjustment.
[0m[49m[39m  320, 336[0m:[39m[49m         actual_end = event.timestamp
[0m[49m[39m  321, 337[0m:[39m[49m         expected_end = current_schedule[event.case_id].expected_end
[0m[49m[39m  322, 338[0m:[39m[49m         deviation = actual_end - expected_end
[0m[49m[39m  323, 339[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  324, 340[0m:[39m[49m         IF abs(deviation) > REPLAN_THRESHOLD_MINUTES:  // e.g., 15 minutes
[0m[49m[39m  325, 341[0m:[39m[49m             enqueue_replan(reason = "duration_deviation", deviation = deviation)
[0m[49m[39m  326, 342[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  327, 343[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE IF event.type == "case_cancelled":
[0m[49m[39m  328, 344[0m:[39m[49m         // A cancelled case frees room time. Replan to fill the gap.
[0m[49m[39m  329, 345[0m:[39m[49m         enqueue_replan(reason = "cancellation", freed_minutes = case.expected_duration)
[0m[49m[39m  330, 346[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  331, 347[0m:[39m[49m     ELSE IF event.type == "add_on_case":
[0m[49m[39m  332, 348[0m:[39m[49m         // New case needs to be inserted into today's schedule.
[0m[49m[39m  333, 349[0m:[39m[49m         enrich_case(event.case_data)
[0m[49m[39m  334, 350[0m:[39m[49m         enqueue_replan(reason = "add_on", urgency = event.case_data.priority)
[0m[49m[39m  335, 351[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  336, 352[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION enqueue_replan(reason, **kwargs):
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 337     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Send to SQS with deduplication to prevent replan storms.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 338     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // If multiple events arrive within 60 seconds, batch them into one replan.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 339     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     send to replan queue with deduplication_id = "replan-" + current_minute()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Send to SQS FIFO queue with deduplication.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // The 5-minute deduplication window means rapid-fire events within 5 minutes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // of the first replan request are automatically deduplicated by SQS.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Use a time-window-based deduplication ID to batch nearby events.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dedup_window = floor(current_timestamp / 300)  // 5-minute windows
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     send to replan FIFO queue with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         message_group_id = "or-replan"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         deduplication_id = "replan-" + string(dedup_window)
[0m[49m[39m  340, 361[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  341, 362[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  342, 363[0m:[39m[49m **Step 5: Publish and visualize.** The optimized schedule is exposed via API for the OR dashboard, EHR integration, and mobile notifications to surgical teams.
[0m[49m[39m  343, 364[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  344, 365[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  345, 366[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION publish_schedule(schedule):
[0m[49m[39m  346, 367[0m:[39m[49m     // Write to API-accessible format.
[0m[49m[39m  347, 368[0m:[39m[49m     FOR each room in schedule.rooms:
[0m[49m[39m  348, 369[0m:[39m[49m         room_timeline = {
[0m[49m[39m  349, 370[0m:[39m[49m             room_id:    room.id,
[0m[49m[39m  350, 371[0m:[39m[49m             room_name:  room.display_name,
[0m[49m[39m  351, 372[0m:[39m[49m             cases: [
[0m[49m[39m  352, 373[0m:[39m[49m                 {
[0m[49m[39m  353, 374[0m:[39m[49m                     case_id:     case.id,
[0m[49m[39m  354, 375[0m:[39m[49m                     procedure:   case.procedure_name,
[0m[49m[39m  355, 376[0m:[39m[49m                     surgeon:     case.surgeon_name,
[0m[49m[39m  356, 377[0m:[39m[49m                     start_time:  case.optimized_start,
[0m[49m[39m  357, 378[0m:[39m[49m                     end_time:    case.optimized_end,
[0m[49m[39m  358, 379[0m:[39m[49m                     status:      case.current_status,
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 359     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m                     confidence:  case.schedule_confidence  // how likely this time holds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     confidence:  case.schedule_confidence,  // how likely this time holds
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     is_locked:   case.has_manual_override   // visually distinguish overrides
[0m[49m[39m  360, 382[0m:[39m[49m                 }
[0m[49m[39m  361, 383[0m:[39m[49m                 FOR each case in room.sequence
[0m[49m[39m  362, 384[0m:[39m[49m             ]
[0m[49m[39m  363, 385[0m:[39m[49m         }
[0m[49m[39m  364, 386[0m:[39m[49m         write room_timeline to API cache
[0m[49m[39m  365, 387[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  366, 388[0m:[39m[49m     // Notify affected staff of schedule changes (if this was a replan).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Use a HIPAA-compliant channel: push notification to a secured mobile app
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // (preferred), pager with case ID only (no patient name), or encrypted email.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Avoid SMS with patient-identifiable content. Notifications contain the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // minimum necessary: case ID, new time, new room. Staff look up patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // details in the secured dashboard.
[0m[49m[39m  367, 394[0m:[39m[49m     IF schedule.is_replan:
[0m[49m[39m  368, 395[0m:[39m[49m         changed_cases = find cases where start_time or room changed
[0m[49m[39m  369, 396[0m:[39m[49m         FOR each case in changed_cases:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 370     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m             notify surgical team (surgeon, anesthesia, nursing) of new time/room
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             send_secure_notification(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 recipients = case.surgical_team,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 content = { case_id: case.id, new_room: case.room, new_time: case.start }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             )
[0m[49m[39m  371, 401[0m:[39m[49m ```
[0m[49m[39m  372, 402[0m:[39m[49m 
